President Trump arrived in Israel and was welcomed by President Rivlin. They both delivered remarks, with President Rivlin expressing happiness that "America is back in the area." President Trump thanked President Rivlin and reaffirmed the enduring friendship between the US and Israel. He also spoke about strengthening trade and commerce ties between the two countries. President Trump will spend the day in Israel, including a visit with Prime Minister Netanyahu and a visit to the Western Wall, where he became the first sitting President to pray and place a prayer in the wall.